 ${misc:Depends},
 python3 (>= 3.11),
 python3-gi,
 gir1.2-webkit2-4.1 | gir1.2-webkit2-4.0,
 ollama
Description: Vibbey AI assistant service for VibeOS
 Vibbey is the VibeOS onboarding assistant — a Clippy-lineage AI guide
 that greets the user on first login, walks through hardware detection,
 and hands off to Claude Code once the user is ready.
 .
 Ships the Vibbey Python source at /usr/share/vibeos/vibbey/, the static
 web UI (Three.js scene + chat), the /etc/vibeos/vibbey.conf single-config
 file, the vibbey.service systemd unit, and the XDG autostart entry for
 first-login detection. Requires Ollama (installed separately).
 .
 The active AI model is controlled by VIBEOS_MODEL in vibbey.conf.
 Default: qwen2.5:3b (pre-pulled into the ISO at build time).
